description: Try to Set the Version of SED to the Master Version on signam without permissions
args: sed_update --user lciadm100 --sedVersion 99.99.99
expectedOut: ERROR: User: lciadm100 is not authorised to write to modify Master, please try again or register user

description: Try to Set the Version of SED to the Master Version on signam without permissions and registerUser set to no
args: sed_update --user lciadm100 --sedVersion 99.99.99 --registerUser no
expectedOut: ERROR: User: lciadm100 is not authorised to write to modify Master, please try again or register user

description: Register user to have permissions to Set the Version of SED to the Master Version and Set
args: sed_update --user lciadm100 --sedVersion 99.99.99 --registerUser yes
expectedOut: SUCCESS: SED version: 99.99.99 set to master SED

description: Set the same Version of SED to the Master Version again
args: sed_update --user lciadm100 --sedVersion 99.99.99
expectedOut: This Version of SED is already set to Master, nothing to do

description: Try to Set the Version of SED to the Master with user parameter missing
args: sed_update --sedVersion 99.99.99
